summary: An ordinance accepting a deed from Walter E. Mitchell and Emma Mitchell, his wife, to the City of Seattle, dated April 9, 1909, to a right of way to construct, maintain and operate a sewer with the necessary appurtenances, over, through, across and upon the following described property, situated in King County, Washington, particularly described as follows: a strip of land 3 feet wide, on the south side of lot 16, block 4, Hunter's Lake Union Addition, beginning in the middle and to extend to the east end of said lot.
